  <a href="#1" id="1">
   THE STORY OF AQUINO
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   President Corazon Aquino on Aug. 29, 1990 reversed a long-held policy and said she was willing to negotiate cease-fires with Communist guerrillas and former soldiers who have staged coup attempts.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Mrs. Aquino said in a statement on Aug. 29, 1990 that Mercado and Enrile are welcome to join discussions now being held by a committee of Cabinet members.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Sen. Wigberto Tanada called for a truce between the government and the Communist rebels after a major earthquake in the Philippines on July 16, but Mrs. Aquino rejected the proposal.
  </a>
